My dotfiles - by Henrique Gogó

Installation:

  - Clone the repository
  - Create symbolic links for each dot file

Files:

  .tmux.conf - Changes prefix to C-a and set some colors and default settings

  .muttrc - Default configuration for Gmail accounts.
  Create a .mutt/local file to set realname, imap_user and imap_pass

  .lynxrc - Vi keymaps, nvim editor and accept cookies

  .gitconfig - Set user, email and diff tool

    $ git history
    Show git log in terminal with some format and colors

    $ git sync
    Update all repositories in a folder

  .bash_aliases - Prompt config and bash functions

    $ google "Why the sky is blue"
    Search in google using lynx terminal browser. Quotes are optional

    $ loadenv ./folder
    Load folder into env variables. ./bin into $PATH, ./lib into
    $LD_LIBRARY_PATH and others. Auto add every ~/opt/* as default

    $ confine ./folder
    Start chroot with clean environment. Automount /proc

  .vimrc - Vim and NeoVim default settings, theme, commands and functions

    - Netrw can be used as a file explorer :Lexplorer
    - Default theme colors based on onedark theme
    - Personalized statusline
    - Buffers and tab navigation keymaps
    - Insert chars in line beginning. Works in normal and visual mode.
      Good for comment a line: <Space>0
    - Surround keymaps: <Space>', <Space>", <Space>(, <Space>{, <Space>[
    - Begining words and surround chars can be removed using double char:
      <Space>00, <Space>'' 

    :Find
    Use shell "find" command to search file names recursively.
    Keymap: <Leader>e

    :Search
    Use shell "rg" or "grep" command to search text in files recursively.
    Keymap: <Leader>/

    :PluginInstall, :PluginRemove, :PluginUpdate, :PluginList
    Manage plugins into packages folder.
    Alternative syntax: "call PluginInstall('author/plugin')"

Disclaimer:

  These are my personal settings. You can use them as you wish,
  but I use to change it a lot sometimes.
